</taxonomicName>
Montroux, but differing in its high elevation serpentine substrate habitat, very fleshy, semi-succulent stems and leaves, glabrous petioles and larger berries.
</paragraph>
<caption id="14139F04FA49098D231FE4BAD79D1E8E" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.145.48531.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/398919" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 11" startId="F11">
